76561198025884001,Recommended,263360,8705822,"Posted: 14 January, 2014",all,DREW,"After 6 hours of gameplay, I'm still finding new game features.  You can customize your character, your weapons, your strategy... your entire gaming experience.  That may sound cumbersome, but the customization is actually very fluid and intuitive.  The story is a bit weak in the beginning, but it's getting more interesting.  The story advances a little bit every time you track down and defeat a boss.  Boss battles aren't easy, so you need to train and level-up a bit beforehand.The quest system is pretty lame, though.  Quests are randomly generated; they have no story; they don't effect the larger game world in any meaningful way.  Quests just give you skill points to improve your character.  Some people will compare this game to Borderlands, which is fair up to a point.  However, Borderlands goes far beyond this game in terms of character customization, special abilities, cool features, etc.I bought this game for $7, and it was worth it."
,Recommended,263360,8759686,"Posted: 18 January, 2014",all,dood.,"Give this game a shot based on the gameplay it offers rather than the graphical presentation. Personally, I enjoy the simple graphics as it adds a somewhat nostalgic feel to the game's environment. Also, all graphical elements are moddable through the .jar file and the ease of modding the game is highly encouraged by the game's developer.Gameplay OverviewIt combines the addictiveness of Diablo/Borderlands' weapon and armor randomization with the procedurally generated terrain such as in Minecraft and achieves it very successfully. In addition, you can break and combine parts of armor and weapons.Yes, there are grappling hooks, gravity guns, and teleportation devices. As well as decoy guns, turrets, and other interesting devices.The limitless terrain is awesome and lets you take any path you wish for as long as you want. You can choose to just explore at your own will or take upon randomized quests with varying lengths and failure conditions. There are randomly generated battles between robots (NPCs), ""dungeons"", terrestrial anomalies, biomes, weather and it all flows really smoothly.You will find very quickly that enemies will shred you apart if you do not make good use of cover and later on, if you neglect defensive stats (stealth or armor/hp). The enemies provide the right amount of challenge while not being too ridiculously powerful or weak.Death penalty is currently losing one random item in your inventory, equipped or not. So don't yolo without keeping a storage of important items (requires a building tool, unlocked during the story quests).Make sure you find all the ""back-up"" nodes inside buildings and save at a location where you'll be spending alot of time at. You do not want to painstakingly go all the way back to where you were from the starting location.CustomizationYou might not see or think much any level of character customization until you open up your character stats then it hits you like a truck.There are plenty of ways to build your character in terms of gameplay style (of course you can mix and match all of these as you wish...or just master them all):recruiting masses of robotsguns (pistols, rifles, launchers) (Energy and ballistic)melee (sword and dagger)stealthpiloting aircraftpickpocketting (!)There are also improvable supplementary stats such as consumable efficiency, reprogramming chip equipment and the standard health, armor, energy.Weapons can come with a plethora of effects such as a corrosion effect (damage over time), homing, explosive radius, shot speed, shot distance, varying ammo consumpion, ammo per reload, stat boosts and more.Most of your additional stats will come from armor, as well as protection from radiation.Also, hoverboards. ReBoot ANYONE?StorySuper-short summary: You are a test subject robot dropped into a world to see if ""emotion"" is capable of overcoming regular robot odds.The story fits quite nicely with the theme of the game and serves as a great guiding tool for those less inclined to randomly stroll about the world with no direct feedback. You will need to advance a bit into the story to gain access to one of the more interesting features of this game: the building tool.Be careful about advancing through the story too quickly, you may find yourself in the middle of a big...surprise.MultiplayerCurrently the game supports two player co-op which I have yet to try. You may have to open port 3089 on your firewall and/or router. Games hosted will be announced on the dev's twitter if public is set to on."
