,Recommended,263360,8697266,"Posted: 13 January, 2014",all,Chiriam,"This is a game that really surprised me. At first glance I didn't really think much of it, and to be fair it is not much to look at. However, the gameplay is actually quite entertaining. Some of the more pronounced strengths of the game to me, in no particualr order, is:1: The randomly generated world. It creates diversity, and the terrain generator is quite capable of creating interesting terrain.2: The loot comes in parts than can be picked apart and reassembled at workstations, making you at least somewhat interested in what you pick up. It could use a little bit more weapon type variety though, especially in the melee department.3: The Time Rip ability. When you wander the world, there are little clocks to collect that spawn all over the place. It fills up a meter you can use to stop time for at max 15 seconds. I don't think I have to say how useful this is if something goes wrong.4: As you advance in the main quest, more enemy variety is introduced, which helps keep up the interest. And you do indeed notice the difference...5: Unlimited skillpoints. The quests from quest stations are randomly generated and provide skillpoints, so you are allowed to waste points in stats that don't promote your ability to fight.6: And lastly, the special weapons category. Hoverboards, grappling hooks, blink tech, decoys. ect. It really makes it more fun to move about, which is a huge plus! Especially when a meteor shower starts and you have to rush to a place with a roof. Tip: If one player has a hoverboard, the other player can request to be a gunner, combining the two players so that both can make use of the hoverboard. It's hilarious.All in all, I was really surpised I liked it as much as I did, and even the graphics have really grown on me. I am looking forward to what other things this game has in store for me. Fingers crossed for more weapon variety and some more special items!"
