76561198054670377,Recommended,263360,9032393,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,DesTroll,"Oh hell yeah!Don't let the dated graphics fool you, 3089 is an awesome game.It may seem shallow on the surface, but if you give it a little bit of your time to test it out, the next thing you know several hours will have passed.So run around for a bit, blow some stuff up, and get some of the crazy loot.Just be careful out there on Xax.The enemies might border on being stupid, but their aim is deadly as hell.Charge up your energy rifle and watch those little blue robots melt.Sword dash ***through the air*** and pummel flying gunships up close and personal.Take a mad dash across the country-side on a speedy little HOVERBOARD! (I've wanted one of those since the first time I saw Back to the Future 2!!!)Grappling hooks, grenade launchers, pistols, daggers, your own pet robots that follow you around, sniper rifles, armor, pilotable aircraft...This game has a ton of things to see and do to keep you entertained for hours.And nearly every last iota of it is procedurally generated.As far as I can tell the starting area's building layout is always the same, but everything inside of it, just like the rest of the world, is randomly generated as you go along.The world never ends, but the further you travel from the start point, the more difficult the enemies become.Quests will reward you with the currency used in the game, and while it's easy enough to save up those credits, you can burn through them real fast.Quests willl also give you the skill points you'll need to allocate to all your different stats.That is a big bonus.When you first land on Xax, the quests will offer you 3 to 5 points each for you stats, but the further out you go, the more dangerous the enemies and quests become, and the greater those stat point rewards get.Move out far enough, and eventually all those little guys that scared you silly at the start will seem as insignificant as gnats, making it a very safe place to head back to and relax for a bit.Weapons can be bought (or looted from the corpses of your enemies) preconstructed or in parts and each part has a range of stats and attributes that effect the weapon itself and/or buff your character.Those parts can be mixed and matched at any workbench to make your own ultimate weapons.On top of all that, if you find the parts and have enough resources you can even start constructing your own buildings, fortresses, and defenses.Want to build your own castle? Why not, go for it.How about constructing a bunch of turrets to make a defensive perimeter while you're at it too.Seriously, just stop reading this now.If you can afford it, buy the game, try it out.Unless you have a very strong disdain for stat and loot grinding or dated graphics, you'll probably have more fun with it than you expect."
