76561198042956737,Not Recommended,263360,13938401,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,atramentousFirmament,"I was optimistic about this game.  It's got a procedurally generated open world, it's got robots, it's got action RPG mechanics, it's got shooting, it's got equipment customization and aircraft piloting, it's got stealth, it's got procedurally generated missions, it's got time manipulation mechanics, it's got ♥♥♥♥ing everything.  That's just it, though.  It's spread so thin.  There are so many cool individual ideas and mechanics in this game, but not a single one of them is done well.  The ""action"" is slow, piloting an aircraft somehow manages to be just as uninteresting as walking, the rpg mechanics are boring and uninspired, the stealth is crap, the fps mechanics are crap, and the big world you're given to explore lacks anything worth exploring.  Obviously, having only played 1.3 hours, I can't tell you how the late game plays.  I can, however, tell you that the first 1.3 hours are astonishingly dull.  Even the base being bombarded with meteors was boring, all it means is you have to sit in a tastelessly coloured ""house"" for a while.That's another thing, the visuals.  Obviously I wasn't expecting anything gorgeous, I saw the screenshots.  Keep in mind, however, that what you see in the screenshots is the best that the game has to offer in the visual department.  The environments are woefully underpopulated with any kind of visually interesting scenery.  Every other aspect of the fluff is equally lacking: missions have no flavour, enemies and allies alike lack even a slight amount of personality, etc.TL;DR:Describing the environment is, perhaps, one of the best ways of describing the game on a whole: an ambitiously vast expanse of nothing."
