,Recommended,263360,12379966,"Posted: 5 October, 2014",all,"mess with Chen, get the horns","Overall 3089 has a good story and excellent gameplay, but there are some lackings. The stealth mechanics are too costly and pretty slow, while more hotkeys for weapons could be welcome. The ""jobs for experience"" system is very simple, easy to do, but take a bit of care because of restrictions. They might be repetitive for some people, but they are incredibly simple and use the core game mechanics in effective ways.The game could be improved a bit and expanded heavily, but on its own it's pretty fun. I'd suggest to get it on sale, as the author intends to add more depth and complexity in the sequel.Almost forgot: The co-op is probably one of the best aspects of the game. Unfortunately it's only two-player, but it is easy to manage and having both players aids in exploration and you can contribute to the jobs of your partner (but you don't get any experience)."
